BLUEHOC is a Bluetooth*(TM) extension to Network simulator (ns-2.1b7a)
(www.isi.edu/nsnam/ns)

BLUEHOC requires ns-2.1b7a 

It simulates the basic features of the 
following Bluetooth layers:
(1) Baseband
(2) Link Manager Protocol.(LMP) 
(3) Logical link adaptation and control protcol.(L2CAP) 

This release is bluehoc2.0

BLUEHOC is available under IBM Public License (IPL) from 
IBM developerWorks (oss.software.ibm.com/developerworks/projects/bluehoc). 

Please see the presentation and BlueHoc manual on the site: 
(oss.software.ibm.com/developerworks/opensource/bluehoc)
to know more about the Bluetooth functionalities implemented 
in BLUEHOC. 







